result.title: Help me CF
result.content:
Hello CF, please help me to solve this problem:

A and B given, find count numbers in [A,B] which can be represented as multiplication of 3 prime numbers. 1 ≤ A, B ≤ 10000000.

Example: A = 10, B = 20 then, answer is 3, i.e. (12, 18, 20) (12 = 2 * 2 * 3, 18 = 2 * 3 * 3, 20 = 2 * 2 * 5)

Time limit is 1 second.
